00:12:09,563 --> 00:12:12,288
I unfortunately
        do not eat meat.

249
00:12:12,381 --> 00:12:13,973
It's not meat, it's sausage.
            Now eat.

250
00:12:14,067 --> 00:12:16,401
[bright lively music]

251
00:12:16,552 --> 00:12:17,318
[♪♪]

252
00:12:22,133 --> 00:12:23,324
[sighs]

253
00:12:24,727 --> 00:12:27,203
-Can I ask you a question?
             -Shoot.

254
00:12:28,231 --> 00:12:29,414
You homeless?

255
00:12:31,901 --> 00:12:33,476
Why would you ask me that?

256
00:12:33,569 --> 00:12:35,236
The, the camper,
        the sleeping bag,

257
00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:37,313
And no disrespect, your honor,

258
00:12:37,406 --> 00:12:39,382
But you look like
     you have not showered.

259
00:12:40,819 --> 00:12:42,093
[kim sniffs]

260
00:12:43,764 --> 00:12:46,656
I take a bath regularly
  if that's what you're asking.

261
00:12:46,674 --> 00:12:48,683
I can help you find a place
          if you need.

262
00:12:50,512 --> 00:12:53,754
No thanks. I like to sleep
   where I can see the stars.

263
00:12:54,332 --> 00:12:55,756
All right, but you know
        that judge brewer

264
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:57,333
Received death threats?

265
00:12:57,426 --> 00:12:59,669
Yeah. And he died
       of a heart attack.

266
00:12:59,762 --> 00:13:01,671
Clearly,
   I can take care of myself.

267
00:13:01,689 --> 00:13:03,281
This ain't vegas.

268
00:13:03,508 --> 00:13:04,524
We don't even
      have metal detectors,

269
00:13:04,676 --> 00:13:06,934
And you met mae.
   She is hardly a deterrent.

270
00:13:07,679 --> 00:13:09,603
But then I have you, don't I?

271
00:13:09,623 --> 00:13:10,914
[vicky chuckles]

272
00:13:13,034 --> 00:13:15,535
[engine rumbling]

273
00:13:15,687 --> 00:13:16,686
Your honor, what should I do

274
00:13:16,779 --> 00:13:19,022
If I witness a crime
       as it's happening?

275
00:13:19,115 --> 00:13:21,466
I guess take the action
          most prudent.

276
00:13:21,693 --> 00:13:22,950
All right then.
   Can you slow the hell down?

277
00:13:23,044 --> 00:13:25,711
You are doing well over 100.

278
00:13:25,806 --> 00:13:28,531
[laughs] sorry.

279
00:13:28,550 --> 00:13:30,308
No, you're not.

280
00:13:30,535 --> 00:13:34,312
[laughs] well, would
        you look at that?

281
00:13:35,131 --> 00:13:37,373
Uh, yeah, the
       tonopah solar farms

282
00:13:37,466 --> 00:13:40,301
Owned by the one and only
         bart crawford.

283
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:44,656
-Any kin of dirk?
   -Yeah, his dear old daddy.

284
00:13:45,659 --> 00:13:48,384
[gentle upbeat music]

285
00:13:48,403 --> 00:13:53,456
[♪♪]

286
00:14:03,826 --> 00:14:06,302
[birds chirping]

287
00:14:08,181 --> 00:14:10,239
You are not sleeping
     in this truck tonight.

288
00:14:10,258 --> 00:14:13,242
Why are you so concerned
 about where I get my 40 winks?

289
00:14:13,261 --> 00:14:16,354
Well, because like how you said,
      it is kind of my job.

290
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:19,749
[gentle upbeat music]

291
00:14:19,767 --> 00:14:23,278
Okay, fine, fine. Fine.

292
00:14:25,256 --> 00:14:28,032
But then I'm sleeping in here,
  too. You got another blanket?

293
00:14:30,778 --> 00:14:33,538
-[kim sighs]
         -[vicky grunts]

294
00:14:33,765 --> 00:14:36,616
Well, does the room
     at least have a window?

295
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:38,784
Oh, a big beautiful window
   with views of the mountain.

296
00:14:38,879 --> 00:14:42,714
You'll love it. Come on.

297
00:14:42,865 --> 00:14:47,802
[♪♪]

298
00:14:50,448 --> 00:14:51,723
-It's just down the hall.
           -Thank you.

299
00:14:51,874 --> 00:14:52,807
Have a nice day.

300
00:14:57,063 --> 00:15:00,123
We are in luck. Our rooms
    are on the second floor.

301
00:15:00,141 --> 00:15:01,065
Oh.

302
00:15:01,217 --> 00:15:02,642
Rumor has it
    the third one's haunted.

303
00:15:02,736 --> 00:15:04,794
Oh, my kind of place.

304
00:15:04,812 --> 00:15:06,220
What do you say we
      get a drink later on?

305
00:15:06,314 --> 00:15:08,722
-Yeah.
    -[electricity crackling]

306
00:15:08,742 --> 00:15:10,891
Hmm, hope you're okay
          with ghosts.

307
00:15:10,985 --> 00:15:12,985
Oh, dead doesn't bother me.

308
00:15:13,138 --> 00:15:14,728
It's the living
    that gives me the creeps.

309
00:15:14,748 --> 00:15:15,896
Vicky:
               Mm.

310
00:15:15,990 --> 00:15:18,141
[gentle upbeat music continues]

311
00:15:18,159 --> 00:15:20,309
[hands tapping]

312
00:15:21,146 --> 00:15:22,995
Evening, ma'am.
       What's your poison?

313
00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:24,997
-Well, hi there...
             -Vance.

314
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:27,408
Vance, uh, well,
   I prefer an old fashioned,

315
00:15:27,502 --> 00:15:29,986
But I'll settle on a diet soda.

316
00:15:30,004 --> 00:15:32,079
-Coming right up.
           -Thank you.

317
00:15:32,915 --> 00:15:34,581
Customer:
  Hey, vance, you got my order?

318
00:15:34,601 --> 00:15:37,677
Sure do.
   There's your bottle, buddy.

319
00:15:37,829 --> 00:15:39,345
Customer:
             Thanks.

320
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:41,164
You sell booze to go?

321
00:15:41,182 --> 00:15:43,332
I didn't realize
   that was still being done.

322
00:15:43,351 --> 00:15:45,276
Yes, ma'am.
  Whatever the customer wants.

323
00:15:46,354 --> 00:15:48,020
Can I ask what brings you
    to our neck of the woods.

324
00:15:48,114 --> 00:15:50,856
Uh, court. I'm the new judge.

325
00:15:51,009 --> 00:15:53,693
The hammer, right?
        Congratulations.

326
00:15:53,787 --> 00:15:54,935
First time in tonopah?

327
00:15:54,955 --> 00:15:58,289
No, I grew up around here.
         How about you?

328
00:15:58,441 --> 00:15:59,440
Born and raised.

329
00:15:59,534 --> 00:16:02,443
Mm. Married, got any family?

330
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:06,372
Eh, there's a special lady,
      but it's complicated.

331
00:16:06,524 --> 00:16:08,257
Yeah, can relate to that.

332
00:16:09,618 --> 00:16:11,785
-Love what you did to the place.
        -Bart: Thank you.

333
00:16:11,805 --> 00:16:16,365
[upbeat lively music]

334
00:16:16,459 --> 00:16:17,624
How about a little splash
           of whiskey

335
00:16:17,719 --> 00:16:19,202
In that drink, your honor?

336
00:16:19,220 --> 00:16:22,463
Not opposed, but I do like
 to know who I'm drinking with.

337
00:16:22,557 --> 00:16:24,131
I'm the owner
     of this establishment,

338
00:16:24,225 --> 00:16:26,042
-Bart crawford.
             -Ah-ha.

339
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:28,969
Well, I'm the judge
       in your son's case,

340
00:16:28,989 --> 00:16:31,489
And any conversation
      outside the courtroom

341
00:16:31,716 --> 00:16:34,659
Would be construed
   as a conflict of interest.

342
00:16:34,810 --> 00:16:37,220
Only interest I have is
 in getting to know you better.

343
00:16:37,238 --> 00:16:38,663
Well, well, if you've got
        something to say,

344
00:16:38,890 --> 00:16:39,889
Go ahead and say it

345
00:16:39,907 --> 00:16:42,058
'cause I'm fixing
      to enjoy my evening.

346
00:16:42,076 --> 00:16:43,576
Just wanna say welcome.

347
00:16:43,728 --> 00:16:45,652
We residents of tonopah
      are thrilled to have

348
00:16:45,672 --> 00:16:48,397
A legal mind of your caliber
          on the bench.

349
00:16:48,491 --> 00:16:50,066
I hope you don't
      mind me saying this,

350
00:16:50,159 --> 00:16:52,401
But you remind me
  of that serpent in the bible.

351
00:16:52,420 --> 00:16:54,661
-Really?
            -Uh-huh.

352
00:16:54,681 --> 00:16:57,740
Well, historically,
     the serpent's a symbol

353
00:16:57,759 --> 00:17:01,260
Of fertility and renewal
       of the life force.

354
00:17:01,412 --> 00:17:02,836
Not very subtle, are you?

355
00:17:02,930 --> 00:17:05,172
-May I?
         -Help yourself.

356
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:06,858
The governor's
        a friend of mine.

357
00:17:07,009 --> 00:17:09,009
When he mentioned your name
    to replace judge brewer,

358
00:17:09,103 --> 00:17:12,012
I endorsed your wholeheartedly.

359
00:17:12,032 --> 00:17:14,515
As a lawyer, no one in this
  state's done more for victims

360
00:17:14,534 --> 00:17:16,609
Of abuse and discrimination
         than you have.

361
00:17:16,761 --> 00:17:18,185
Well, thank you for that.

362
00:17:18,204 --> 00:17:20,204
So, you're a friend
      of the governor, huh?

363
00:17:20,431 --> 00:17:22,874
Bart:
  I am, we, we met in princeton

364
00:17:23,101 --> 00:17:25,451
For my two decades
       in silicon valley.

365
00:17:25,545 --> 00:17:27,436
So you're a techie. [chuckles]

366
00:17:27,530 --> 00:17:29,363
I bet this place
       bores you to tears.

367
00:17:29,457 --> 00:17:30,773
Well, no. On the contrary,

368
00:17:30,866 --> 00:17:33,276
Nevada's a land
     of untapped potential.

369
00:17:33,369 --> 00:17:35,611
I'm very excited
        about being back.

370
00:17:35,630 --> 00:17:38,447
Your honor. Bart.

371
00:17:38,541 --> 00:17:42,134
[grunts] you ladies going
    out on the town tonight?

372
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:43,803
I could arrange a special table.

373
00:17:43,955 --> 00:17:46,064
Thanks, but we're good.

374
00:17:47,642 --> 00:17:49,383
You two enjoy your evening.

375
00:17:49,477 --> 00:17:51,736
Judge wheeler,
     very nice to meet you.

376
00:17:52,888 --> 00:17:54,072
Mr. Crawford.

377
00:17:55,408 --> 00:17:56,632
Bart:
            Victoria.

378
00:17:56,725 --> 00:18:01,153
[laughs] I didn't take you
       for a saloon girl.

379
00:18:01,247 --> 00:18:03,472
Hey, I was just sitting
  here minding my own business.

380
00:18:03,491 --> 00:18:04,415
Sure, but if I was you,

381
00:18:04,567 --> 00:18:06,492
I'd stay away
       from bart crawford.

382
00:18:06,586 --> 00:18:08,920
He's always reminded me
   of that snake in the bible.

383
00:18:10,648 --> 00:18:11,497
Vance.

384
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:14,092
[gentle upbeat music]

385
00:18:14,243 --> 00:18:18,846
[♪♪]

386
00:18:27,332 --> 00:18:28,940
[cellphone ringing]

387
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:31,192
Vicky:
               Mm.

388
00:18:34,005 --> 00:18:34,737
Mm.

389
00:18:37,692 --> 00:18:40,693
[clears throat]
      this better be good.

390
00:18:40,845 --> 00:18:43,679
Friend:
        Hey honey, it is.

391
00:18:43,698 --> 00:18:46,273
The autopsy just came
      back on judge brewer.

392
00:18:46,367 --> 00:18:48,042
It looks like he was
            murdered.

393
00:18:49,354 --> 00:18:50,536
Yeah. Okay, thanks.

394
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:53,356
[dramatic tense music]

395
00:18:53,374 --> 00:18:57,802
[♪♪]

396
00:19:07,981 --> 00:19:11,399
Judge wheeler. Judge wheeler!

397
00:19:14,136 --> 00:19:17,046
What are you,
    some kind of new rooster?

398
00:19:17,064 --> 00:19:18,805
I thought I saw someone
         sneaking about.

399
00:19:18,825 --> 00:19:21,233
Maybe it's the mitzvah ghost.

400
00:19:21,386 --> 00:19:22,809
And you said you'd sleep
       in a room tonight.

401
00:19:22,829 --> 00:19:25,163
I tried, but it was so stuffy.

402
00:19:26,224 --> 00:19:27,740
What are you doing
        down here anyway?

403
00:19:27,834 --> 00:19:29,558
Vicky:
    I just got off the phone
         with a friend.

404
00:19:29,577 --> 00:19:31,335
The autopsy for judge brewer
         just came back.

405
00:19:31,487 --> 00:19:32,578
He was murdered.

406
00:19:32,672 --> 00:19:36,174
[dramatic tense music]

407
00:19:40,013 --> 00:19:41,328
[gentle upbeat music]

408
00:19:41,347 --> 00:19:43,330
-Kim: Good morning.
      -Vicky: Good morning.

409
00:19:43,424 --> 00:19:46,075
-All clean. Wanna check?
          -I trust you.

410
00:19:46,093 --> 00:19:49,020
Okay, so how close
       is the courthouse?

411
00:19:49,171 --> 00:19:51,147
-Eh, I'd say it's pretty close.
            -Mm-hmm.

412
00:19:53,342 --> 00:19:56,027
Judge, I have to say
         I'm concerned.

413
00:19:56,254 --> 00:19:57,586
What about?

414
00:19:57,680 --> 00:19:58,679
Well, we just learned
          that the man

415
00:19:58,698 --> 00:20:00,031
That you replaced was killed,

416
00:20:00,182 --> 00:20:02,700
And then there was a stranger
    in white snakeskin boots

417
00:20:02,851 --> 00:20:05,536
Creeping around your truck
           last night.

418
00:20:05,763 --> 00:20:07,521
How are you completely
      unfazed by all this?

419
00:20:07,615 --> 00:20:09,356
You're not worried
       you could be next?

420
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:12,877
Oh, it's just the way I am,
    calm under the pressure.

421
00:20:13,104 --> 00:20:16,380
So, any more information
     back from your friend?

422
00:20:16,532 --> 00:20:18,716
They have a suspect,
but that's all he could tell me.

423
00:20:18,867 --> 00:20:21,444
Is he a boyfriend?

424
00:20:21,537 --> 00:20:23,870
Oh, we went on a date or two.

425
00:20:23,890 --> 00:20:26,465
-Is he in law enforcement?
         -He's a deputy.

426
00:20:26,617 --> 00:20:28,375
Any more questions
     in this interrogation?

427
00:20:28,394 --> 00:20:30,544
No, not right now, but I'm sure
    I'll think of something.

428
00:20:30,563 --> 00:20:32,480
[both chuckling]

429
00:20:33,458 --> 00:20:35,358
[people chattering indistinctly]

430
00:20:37,812 --> 00:20:39,144
You're right. It is close.

431
00:20:39,239 --> 00:20:40,963
[chuckles] you ready?

432
00:20:40,982 --> 00:20:41,864
Mm-hmm.

433
00:20:43,576 --> 00:20:44,909
Vicky:
            All rise.

434
00:20:46,913 --> 00:20:48,487
Fifth district court
     of the state of nevada

435
00:20:48,581 --> 00:20:49,655
Is now in session.

436
00:20:49,807 --> 00:20:52,250
The honorable kim wheeler
         now presiding.

437
00:20:53,661 --> 00:20:55,086
Y'all sit down.

438
00:20:59,166 --> 00:21:02,242
All right, we've gathered today

439
00:21:02,336 --> 00:21:04,653
To hear a motion
     to dismiss in the case

440
00:21:04,672 --> 00:21:08,432
Of the people v. Dirk crawford
    on the charge of murder.

441
00:21:08,584 --> 00:21:09,842
Okay, I've read the brief.

442
00:21:09,994 --> 00:21:12,995
Any additional information
     for me, mr. Goodlander?

443
00:21:13,014 --> 00:21:14,605
Your honor,
   the late judge brewer acted

444
00:21:14,757 --> 00:21:17,166
With bias towards mr. Crawford
       by denying him bail

445
00:21:17,184 --> 00:21:19,001
And leaving him incarcerated
     these past eight months

446
00:21:19,020 --> 00:21:21,504
Despite the fact
    he poses no flight risk.

447
00:21:21,597 --> 00:21:23,597
Dirk crawford,
    the son of bart crawford,

448
00:21:23,691 --> 00:21:25,265
The one that owns
      the large solar farm

449
00:21:25,359 --> 00:21:26,767
-Along the highway?
        -Yes, your honor,

450
00:21:26,861 --> 00:21:28,101
But I don't see
      how that's relevant.

451
00:21:28,121 --> 00:21:30,679
Well, he possesses the means
       to evade judgment.

452
00:21:30,698 --> 00:21:32,364
I'm gonna side
   with judge brewer on this.

453
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:33,682
What else you got?

454
00:21:33,701 --> 00:21:36,185
Judge wheeler,
   the actions of judge brewer

455
00:21:36,203 --> 00:21:37,962
Denied my client his right
       to a speedy trial,

456
00:21:38,113 --> 00:21:39,188
And every day that goes by

457
00:21:39,206 --> 00:21:41,114
Further prejudices
      mr. Crawford's case.

458
00:21:41,134 --> 00:21:42,949
-In what way?
   -My client's defense hinges

459
00:21:43,044 --> 00:21:44,693
On the testimony
        of eyewitnesses.

460
00:21:44,787 --> 00:21:46,378
Their ability to recall
     the events in question

461
00:21:46,472 --> 00:21:49,640
Could be negatively affected
     by the passage of time.

462
00:21:49,792 --> 00:21:52,551
You're afraid that a bunch
     of small-town teenagers

463
00:21:52,645 --> 00:21:54,036
Won't remember the night

464
00:21:54,129 --> 00:21:55,771
That one of their own
           was killed?

465
00:21:57,132 --> 00:21:59,150
-Your honor, may I approach?
       -Yeah, come on up.

466
00:22:01,637 --> 00:22:03,395
You better start
     acting remorseful, son,

467
00:22:03,489 --> 00:22:04,971
And I mean right now.

468
00:22:05,066 --> 00:22:06,065
With all due respect, judge,

469
00:22:06,217 --> 00:22:07,474
You may not be aware
          of the depth

470
00:22:07,568 --> 00:22:09,976
Of animosity that exists
  between the late judge brewer

471
00:22:10,071 --> 00:22:11,403
And the senior mr. Crawford.

472
00:22:11,556 --> 00:22:13,814
Your honor, this is all
  clearly a calculated attempt

473
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:15,816
To introduce the idea
  that the witnesses scheduled

474
00:22:15,910 --> 00:22:18,060
To testify can't be trusted

475
00:22:18,153 --> 00:22:19,912
To remember events
        as they occurred.

476
00:22:20,006 --> 00:22:23,507
Mr. Goodlander, I may be new,
  but I wasn't born yesterday.

477
00:22:23,659 --> 00:22:25,176
-Motion denied.
         -[gavel thuds]

478
00:22:26,420 --> 00:22:28,429
-Ellis: Told you.
           -Kim: Okay.

479
00:22:29,832 --> 00:22:31,515
In the interest
       of a speedy trial,

480
00:22:31,667 --> 00:22:35,019
We can begin jury
     selection immediately.

481
00:22:35,246 --> 00:22:37,838
-Who does the calendar here?
        -Your assistant.

482
00:22:37,932 --> 00:22:40,841
Crap. I was afraid of that.

483
00:22:40,860 --> 00:22:46,530
All righty then.
   Looks like I'm free Monday.

484
00:22:46,682 --> 00:22:48,774
Monday good with everyone?

485
00:22:48,868 --> 00:22:49,867
-Yes, ma'am.
              -Yes.

486
00:22:50,018 --> 00:22:53,596
Okay, see you boys then.
        Court adjourned.

487
00:22:53,614 --> 00:22:54,872
All rise.

488
00:22:56,709 --> 00:22:58,358
[upbeat lively music]

489
00:22:58,452 --> 00:23:00,711
Thank you. Council.

490
00:23:00,863 --> 00:23:02,505
-See you later.
       -Ellis: Thank you.

491
00:23:04,275 --> 00:23:05,608
Oh, pretty.

492
00:23:05,701 --> 00:23:08,293
Oh, I was meaning to ask you,
     the young man who died,

493
00:23:08,388 --> 00:23:10,388
Was any of his family
     in the courtroom today?

494
00:23:10,615 --> 00:23:13,465
No. He only has an uncle
