00:57:41,459 --> 00:57:42,774
That's daisy.

1224
00:57:42,793 --> 00:57:45,252
-You know this cat?
        -Kim: Yes, I do.

1225
00:57:47,523 --> 00:57:49,298
Home is where the heart is.

1226
00:57:51,469 --> 00:57:53,635
Dad. Oh, my god, dad.

1227
00:57:55,973 --> 00:57:56,955
[phone ringing]

1228
00:57:56,974 --> 00:57:58,699
What's the matter?

1229
00:57:58,717 --> 00:58:00,309
-The nurse is not picking up.
          -[jo gasping]

1230
00:58:03,722 --> 00:58:06,148
-[gentle suspenseful music]
        -[birds chirping]

1231
00:58:06,299 --> 00:58:10,777
[♪♪]

1232
00:58:17,828 --> 00:58:18,994
Daddy!

1233
00:58:21,390 --> 00:58:24,333
Virgil:
       Daisy, here, daisy.

1234
00:58:24,560 --> 00:58:26,168
[kim sighs]

1235
00:58:27,153 --> 00:58:29,004
We can't find daisy.

1236
00:58:36,255 --> 00:58:37,904
[gentle melancholy music]

1237
00:58:37,923 --> 00:58:39,998
Wait, someone killed
         your dad's cat?

1238
00:58:40,017 --> 00:58:41,183
That's serious.

1239
00:58:41,334 --> 00:58:42,518
Yeah, I think
  they were trying to scare me,

1240
00:58:42,745 --> 00:58:45,929
-Throw me off my game.
   -Yeah, but for what reason?

1241
00:58:46,081 --> 00:58:48,098
Well, maybe they don't want me
           to find out

1242
00:58:48,250 --> 00:58:50,025
Who really killed judge brewer.

1243
00:58:50,176 --> 00:58:51,768
Okay, and if you're wrong,

1244
00:58:51,862 --> 00:58:53,529
I mean, you're putting
      your family at risk.

1245
00:58:53,680 --> 00:58:55,772
Okay, I was hoping that
  you would talk to your friend

1246
00:58:55,924 --> 00:58:57,533
At the sheriff's department
           and ask him

1247
00:58:57,684 --> 00:58:59,926
If he wouldn't mind keeping
   an eye on my daddy's ranch.

1248
00:58:59,945 --> 00:59:01,019
Of course.

1249
00:59:01,038 --> 00:59:03,613
I don't want word
      getting back to kris.

1250
00:59:03,707 --> 00:59:06,099
She's got enough to worry about.

1251
00:59:06,118 --> 00:59:08,210
Vicky:
      Judge brewer's wife's
          been waiting.

1252
00:59:10,363 --> 00:59:14,132
Right, I'll go talk with her.
        Is that his junk?

1253
00:59:14,885 --> 00:59:15,884
Yeah.

1254
00:59:17,037 --> 00:59:20,447
[indistinct chatter]

1255
00:59:20,465 --> 00:59:22,949
-Wish me luck.
     -You're gonna need it.

1256
00:59:22,968 --> 00:59:24,059
Thanks.

1257
00:59:27,547 --> 00:59:30,640
-Ms. Brewer?
              -Yes.

1258
00:59:30,793 --> 00:59:32,734
I'm kim wheeler,
         the new judge.

1259
00:59:33,796 --> 00:59:35,128
Oh.

1260
00:59:35,147 --> 00:59:38,222
I understand your husband
   was a kind man, well-liked.

1261
00:59:38,242 --> 00:59:42,135
[scoffs] for some.
        These his things?

1262
00:59:42,154 --> 00:59:44,729
Yes, forgive me for being
     indelicate, ms. Brewer,

1263
00:59:44,748 --> 00:59:46,564
But were you aware
        that your husband

1264
00:59:46,584 --> 00:59:48,250
Liked to visit the shady lady?

1265
00:59:49,494 --> 00:59:51,144
With your tramp sister?

1266
00:59:51,237 --> 00:59:53,237
I know kris didn't lead
         a sacred life,

1267
00:59:53,257 --> 00:59:54,923
But she's no killer, ms. Brewer.

1268
00:59:55,150 --> 00:59:56,499
There's no telling
      what a piece of trash

1269
00:59:56,652 --> 00:59:57,834
Like that is capable of.

1270
00:59:57,986 --> 01:00:00,320
I know my sister and she swears

1271
01:00:00,339 --> 01:00:02,322
She did not give your husband
           any drugs.

1272
01:00:02,341 --> 01:00:05,325
Oh, she would do anything
       to destroy our love

1273
01:00:05,344 --> 01:00:07,728
-And ruin our marriage.
    -What makes you say that?

1274
01:00:09,422 --> 01:00:13,775
Two years ago, I found out
   jacob was having an affair.

1275
01:00:14,002 --> 01:00:15,852
He confessed
   and was granted forgiveness

1276
01:00:16,004 --> 01:00:18,530
By the good lord and myself.

1277
01:00:19,950 --> 01:00:21,174
Two weeks ago,

1278
01:00:21,193 --> 01:00:23,285
I found this letter
      in his jacket pocket.

1279
01:00:26,957 --> 01:00:28,606
An unsigned love letter?

1280
01:00:28,700 --> 01:00:32,369
From your sister
     begging him to return,

1281
01:00:32,521 --> 01:00:35,422
And when he didn't,
     she killed him, mm-hmm.

1282
01:00:36,300 --> 01:00:37,549
And there's the proof.

1283
01:00:39,303 --> 01:00:41,470
Have you shown this
         to the sheriff?

1284
01:00:41,697 --> 01:00:43,096
I, I meant to, uh...

1285
01:00:44,975 --> 01:00:47,309
Some reason
  I just couldn't part with it.

1286
01:00:48,871 --> 01:00:52,463
Maybe because both of us know
  my sister didn't write this.

1287
01:00:52,483 --> 01:00:53,899
I'll make sure
      the sheriff gets it.

1288
01:00:55,227 --> 01:01:00,280
I'm sorry for your loss.
      Thanks for coming by.

1289
01:01:04,052 --> 01:01:07,737
[tense suspenseful music]

1290
01:01:07,890 --> 01:01:09,414
How did you know it was me?

1291
01:01:11,076 --> 01:01:12,167
Your handwriting.

1292
01:01:12,394 --> 01:01:14,895
I'd recognize
   that fancy script anywhere.

1293
01:01:16,064 --> 01:01:19,249
I wrote that letter
   after jacob and I broke up.

1294
01:01:19,343 --> 01:01:22,493
-How long were you two together?
           -Two years.

1295
01:01:22,513 --> 01:01:25,496
But I was in love with him
    for a decade before that.

1296
01:01:25,516 --> 01:01:27,349
And his wife never knew
           it was you?

1297
01:01:27,500 --> 01:01:29,092
Jacob protected me

1298
01:01:29,186 --> 01:01:31,186
Even after dottie asked him
        to break it off.

1299
01:01:33,598 --> 01:01:37,842
Did you two ever engage
      in any kind of games,

1300
01:01:37,861 --> 01:01:40,696
-Use drugs, rohypnol?
           -No, never.

1301
01:01:42,849 --> 01:01:43,773
What'd you do
       when you found out

1302
01:01:43,926 --> 01:01:45,926
That he was going
       to the shady lady?

1303
01:01:45,944 --> 01:01:50,122
I didn't know.
    Not until after he died.

1304
01:01:51,266 --> 01:01:53,191
Okay, let me get this straight.

1305
01:01:53,210 --> 01:01:55,268
He strung you along,
         then dumped you

1306
01:01:55,361 --> 01:01:56,286
And went back to his wife,

1307
01:01:56,438 --> 01:01:59,122
And you begged
       for another chance,

1308
01:01:59,216 --> 01:02:02,551
Yet he would rather
     hang out at a brothel?

1309
01:02:02,778 --> 01:02:04,553
You must have been madder
        than all get out.

1310
01:02:04,704 --> 01:02:06,221
Try heartbroken.

1311
01:02:07,373 --> 01:02:10,892
I loved jake,
     and I didn't kill him.

1312
01:02:11,044 --> 01:02:12,060
Then who did?

1313
01:02:12,287 --> 01:02:14,804
[sobs] a lot of people
       didn't like jacob.

1314
01:02:14,898 --> 01:02:17,733
He got threats just like you.

1315
01:02:17,884 --> 01:02:20,902
Most of them were anonymous
   and he never reported them.

1316
01:02:22,314 --> 01:02:25,482
He always said if someone
      didn't want you dead,

1317
01:02:25,634 --> 01:02:27,058
Then you weren't doing your job.

1318
01:02:27,077 --> 01:02:30,078
So, do you think he was killed
  because of one of his cases?

1319
01:02:31,306 --> 01:02:33,248
I honestly don't know.

1320
01:02:35,494 --> 01:02:37,978
Please believe me, judge.

1321
01:02:37,996 --> 01:02:42,090
[gentle suspenseful music]

1322
01:02:44,503 --> 01:02:47,504
Kris:
  Do you think this love letter
       will help clear me?

1323
01:02:47,656 --> 01:02:50,081
Well, it's enough to bring up
   reasonable doubt at trial,

1324
01:02:50,100 --> 01:02:52,434
But I doubt the da'll
        drop the charges.

1325
01:02:52,585 --> 01:02:54,919
Glad you're both here.
     Discovery came through.

1326
01:02:55,013 --> 01:02:56,438
-Did you get the autopsy report?
            -Mm-hmm.

1327
01:02:56,665 --> 01:03:00,834
Forensic shows judge brewer died
 from an overdose of oxycontin.

1328
01:03:00,852 --> 01:03:03,019
Administered intravenously
     under the hallux nail.

1329
01:03:03,113 --> 01:03:04,354
-The what?
        -The big toenail.

1330
01:03:04,506 --> 01:03:06,597
That's where they can hide
       the injection mark.

1331
01:03:06,691 --> 01:03:08,116
You mean like a junkie?

1332
01:03:08,268 --> 01:03:12,270
That explains the rohypnol.
  Judge brewer's a big old boy.

1333
01:03:12,289 --> 01:03:13,771
For the killer to inject him,

1334
01:03:13,791 --> 01:03:15,365
He'd have to incapacitate
           him first.

1335
01:03:15,459 --> 01:03:17,108
Meaning whoever did this

1336
01:03:17,202 --> 01:03:19,461
Likely has experience
         with iv drugs.

1337
01:03:19,688 --> 01:03:21,871
-Kim: Mm-hmm.
   -Which I definitely do not.

1338
01:03:22,024 --> 01:03:23,256
[notification dings]

1339
01:03:25,027 --> 01:03:26,617
Crap. I gotta be somewhere.

1340
01:03:26,711 --> 01:03:28,428
-Check you later, thanks.
          -Kris: Yeah.

1341
01:03:30,474 --> 01:03:31,973
Melba:
      This is looking good.

1342
01:03:33,035 --> 01:03:36,561
[gentle upbeat music]

1343
01:03:39,316 --> 01:03:40,482
Kim:
    So, you two make a deal?

1344
01:03:40,633 --> 01:03:42,484
[clears throat]
   that's correct, your honor.

1345
01:03:42,711 --> 01:03:45,278
-Okay, thank you so much.
            -Welcome.

1346
01:03:48,400 --> 01:03:51,568
So, your client agrees
 to these terms mr. Goodlander?

1347
01:03:51,662 --> 01:03:55,664
Yes, judge. The terms
       are more than fair.

1348
01:03:55,815 --> 01:03:57,073
Okie dokie.

1349
01:03:57,225 --> 01:03:59,835
I'll set sentencing tomorrow
      1:00 p.M. In tonopah.

1350
01:04:01,154 --> 01:04:03,154
-Thank you.
       -Thank you, judge.

1351
01:04:03,173 --> 01:04:05,841
-Ellis, you got a second?
           -Uh, sure.

1352
01:04:07,327 --> 01:04:09,427
-[inhaler whistles]
        -[clears throat]

1353
01:04:10,572 --> 01:04:11,847
So, according to forensics,

1354
01:04:11,998 --> 01:04:13,664
The drug that
       killed judge brewer

1355
01:04:13,758 --> 01:04:15,475
Was injected under the toenail.

1356
01:04:18,246 --> 01:04:19,412
So?

1357
01:04:19,431 --> 01:04:21,189
So, clearly the killer
     was trying to hide it,

1358
01:04:21,416 --> 01:04:24,175
Make it look like
         a heart attack.

1359
01:04:24,194 --> 01:04:27,362
So, we're looking for someone
    with iv drug experience.

1360
01:04:28,940 --> 01:04:30,940
It's a theory,
     but like most theories,

1361
01:04:31,034 --> 01:04:33,109
It's long in imagination,
       short in evidence.

1362
01:04:33,203 --> 01:04:35,261
[laughs]

1363
01:04:35,280 --> 01:04:37,205
It wasn't an accidental
      overdose, counselor.

1364
01:04:37,357 --> 01:04:39,949
It was premeditated.
   You can't just ignore that.

1365
01:04:40,043 --> 01:04:42,043
Are you trying to bully me,
         judge wheeler?

1366
01:04:42,195 --> 01:04:45,005
No, I'm trying to make you
    do your job, mr. Dinkins.

1367
01:04:46,884 --> 01:04:48,550
You have any idea why goodlander

1368
01:04:48,777 --> 01:04:51,052
Was so anxious to settle
       the crawford case?

1369
01:04:51,279 --> 01:04:52,370
Why?

1370
01:04:52,389 --> 01:04:54,948
Because he's worried
      you're a loose cannon

1371
01:04:55,041 --> 01:04:57,283
Running around
     in everyone's business.

1372
01:04:57,377 --> 01:04:59,710
He doesn't trust his case
     with you on the bench.

1373
01:04:59,804 --> 01:05:01,287
That's a bunch of bull.

1374
01:05:01,306 --> 01:05:03,790
He has a weak defense
        and he knows it.

1375
01:05:03,808 --> 01:05:05,642
That may be,

1376
01:05:05,736 --> 01:05:08,144
But I'm gonna tell you
       something for free.

1377
01:05:08,296 --> 01:05:10,572
I'd be careful ruffling
       too many feathers.

1378
01:05:12,242 --> 01:05:13,800
Is that a threat, ellis?

1379
01:05:13,818 --> 01:05:16,036
'cause that sounds
      like a threat to me.

1380
01:05:17,155 --> 01:05:19,155
It's just a friendly
         warning, judge.

1381
01:05:19,249 --> 01:05:24,568
[dramatic tense music]

1382
01:05:24,663 --> 01:05:26,922
Folksy as hell,
       but still a threat.

1383
01:05:31,744 --> 01:05:33,336
[gentle suspenseful music]

1384
01:05:33,488 --> 01:05:34,596
Kim:
      Hey, I need you to go
             through
     the drug court records,

1385
01:05:34,823 --> 01:05:37,081
Compile me a list of
      all the iv drug users

1386
01:05:37,100 --> 01:05:39,750
And then crosscheck that list

1387
01:05:39,844 --> 01:05:42,253
To see if any of them
  are still living in the area.

1388
01:05:42,272 --> 01:05:43,587
How far do you want me
           to go back?

1389
01:05:43,682 --> 01:05:46,499
As far as you can.
 I know it's gonna take a while.

1390
01:05:46,518 --> 01:05:49,260
-Don't worry. I'm on it.
        -Awesome possum.

1391
01:05:49,279 --> 01:05:50,278
[phone beeps]

1392
01:05:50,430 --> 01:05:51,354
So, you really think
         brewer's killer

1393
01:05:51,448 --> 01:05:53,097
Came through drug court?

1394
01:05:53,116 --> 01:05:56,192
Well, it's a lead we definitely
       need to check out.

1395
01:05:56,344 --> 01:05:58,361
If dinkins won't do it,
         that leaves us.

1396
01:05:58,455 --> 01:05:59,621
Mm-hmm.

1397
01:06:05,187 --> 01:06:07,203
Would you say
       I'm a loose cannon?

1398
01:06:07,355 --> 01:06:10,966
No, no, no.

1399
01:06:13,119 --> 01:06:14,952
At least not to your face.

1400
01:06:14,972 --> 01:06:17,222
[laughs]

1401
01:06:18,124 --> 01:06:19,474
Okay, fair enough.

1402
01:06:21,036 --> 01:06:23,203
[gentle upbeat music]

1403
01:06:23,221 --> 01:06:27,315
[♪♪]

1404
01:06:27,467 --> 01:06:29,943
Kim:
 All righty then, mr. Crawford,
     would you please stand?

1405
01:06:31,730 --> 01:06:34,230
Dirk crawford, you are hereby
     sentenced to two years

1406
01:06:34,324 --> 01:06:36,883
In the southern desert
       correctional center

1407
01:06:36,901 --> 01:06:39,744
In indian springs
  with credit for time served.

1408
01:06:42,148 --> 01:06:45,074
Eligibility for parole
    will be at the discretion

1409
01:06:45,227 --> 01:06:47,002
Of the parole board,

1410
01:06:47,229 --> 01:06:48,986
And I'm suspending
      your driver's license

1411
01:06:49,006 --> 01:06:51,989
For one year
      pending your release.

1412
01:06:52,009 --> 01:06:53,008
Thank you, your honor.

1413
01:06:53,159 --> 01:06:54,400
Keep your shirt on,
         mr. Goodlander.

1414
01:06:54,419 --> 01:06:55,510
I'm not finished.

1415
01:06:57,239 --> 01:07:00,473
Mr. Crawford, it's clear to me
that you have issues with anger,

1416
01:07:01,685 --> 01:07:04,352
So I hereby order to you
      to complete 52 hours

1417
01:07:04,504 --> 01:07:09,190
Of anger management classes
      at your own expense,

1418
01:07:09,342 --> 01:07:11,675
And prior to release,
    you will appear before me

1419
01:07:11,695 --> 01:07:13,253
To explain what you've learned

1420
01:07:13,271 --> 01:07:17,532
And why something like this
 will never, ever happen again.

1421
01:07:19,277 --> 01:07:22,262
We'll all make mistakes,
          mr. Crawford,

1422
01:07:22,280 --> 01:07:24,873
But yours cost
      a young man his life,

1423
01:07:25,100 --> 01:07:28,268
Someone who by all accounts
       was a close friend,

1424
01:07:28,361 --> 01:07:33,439
Someone who apparently
     will never get to enjoy

1425
01:07:33,458 --> 01:07:37,052
The opportunities
   that you so easily disdain.

1426
01:07:37,279 --> 01:07:39,946
That young man
   will never have the chance

1427
01:07:39,964 --> 01:07:42,448
To fulfill his promise,

1428
01:07:42,467 --> 01:07:45,060
But you can honor him
      by not wasting yours.

1429
01:07:47,956 --> 01:07:51,232
Do your time, mr. Crawford.
          Make amends.

1430
01:07:51,384 --> 01:07:53,234
And the next time we meet,

1431
01:07:53,386 --> 01:07:58,073
Impress me with your resolve
   to become a better person.

1432
01:08:00,985 --> 01:08:05,914
Because trust this,
 you won't like me disappointed.

1433
01:08:08,660 --> 01:08:10,043
Any objections?

1434
01:08:11,588 --> 01:08:13,421
-No, your honor.
  -Goodlander: No, your honor.

1435
01:08:13,573 --> 01:08:14,923
-We're done here.
         -[gavel thuds]

1436
01:08:16,075 --> 01:08:17,667
Vicky:
            All rise.

1437
01:08:17,819 --> 01:08:21,154
[gentle contemplative music]

1438
01:08:21,172 --> 01:08:23,581
Dirk, this is not gonna
  happen, okay, honey? Just...

1439
01:08:24,917 --> 01:08:26,326
What the hell? You were
 supposed to take care of this.

1440
01:08:26,419 --> 01:08:27,751
What the hell is going on?

1441
01:08:27,771 --> 01:08:28,937
-Be strong.
     -What we're gonna do--

1442
01:08:29,606 --> 01:08:30,997
[charlene sighs]

1443
01:08:31,015 --> 01:08:34,943
[♪♪]

1444
01:08:40,008 --> 01:08:41,341
[sighs]

1445
01:08:41,359 --> 01:08:45,345
Vance, I'm in need
       of your expertise.

1446
01:08:45,363 --> 01:08:47,247
-Old fashioned?
          -You got it.

1447
01:08:48,700 --> 01:08:49,958
[sighs]

1448
01:08:54,189 --> 01:08:55,797
I guess you're
      feeling pretty smug.

1449
01:08:55,948 --> 01:08:57,132
Excuse me?

1450
01:08:57,283 --> 01:08:59,634
Now, you like sitting up
    there all high and mighty

1451
01:08:59,785 --> 01:09:01,118
Passing judgment on people,
           don't you?

1452
01:09:01,138 --> 01:09:04,046
Okay, there's a big difference
    between passing sentence

1453
01:09:04,141 --> 01:09:05,456
And passing judgment.

1454
01:09:05,475 --> 01:09:08,476
My son is going to prison,
    but you insist in piling

1455
01:09:08,628 --> 01:09:10,812
On the embarrassment
   by ordering him to therapy?

1456
01:09:10,963 --> 01:09:12,814
I'm just trying to give dirk
       the tools he needs

1457
01:09:13,041 --> 01:09:15,299
To make him a productive
       member of society.

1458
01:09:15,393 --> 01:09:16,985
You are pathetic.

1459
01:09:17,212 --> 01:09:19,487
-Okay. Lady, you need back off.
            -Or what?

1460
01:09:19,639 --> 01:09:21,731
